  "html": "<div id=\"BUV\" class=\"uplift front\">\n<section id=\"course-front-body\" class=\"responsive-padding\" style=\"color: #2d3b45; background: none; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px;\">\n<article id=\"course-lesson-intro-text\" style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\n<h3 class=\"heavy\" style=\"margin: 0; font-size: 2.7em;\">Designing in Context (A): Territories, Clients and Audiences</h3>\n<p>In this module, students will understand the intersection of narrative, language, and userexperience. Exploring \u2018context\u2019 further will introduce the nuances of audience needs and theimportance of communication environments. The central theme is context-drivencommunication design, highlighting the need to adapt creative choices to the client andmaking meaningful connections between visual language, copy, narrative, and the finalconveyed message.</p>\n</article>\n<div class=\"grid-row\">\n<article class=\"col-lg-4 buv-responsive-video-100\" style=\"padding-left: 12px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-top: 20px;\"><iframe class=\"lti-embed\" style=\"border: none; display: inline-block;\" title=\"2409 NEW Des In Context v1\" src=\"https://buv.instructure.com/courses/3877/external_tools/retrieve?display=borderless&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fbuv.instructuremedia.com%2Flti%2Flaunch%3Fcustom_arc_display_download%3Dtrue%26custom_arc_launch_type%3Dbare_embed%26custom_arc_media_id%3Db1eb2eab-8925-4248-8edc-768cfda8aa5c-26999%26custom_arc_start_at%3D0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"webkitallowfullscreen\" mozallowfullscreen=\"mozallowfullscreen\" allow=\"geolocation *; microphone *; camera *; midi *; encrypted-media *; autoplay *; clipboard-write *; display-capture *\" data-studio-resizable=\"true\" data-studio-tray-enabled=\"true\" data-studio-convertible-to-link=\"true\"></iframe></article>\n<article class=\"col-lg-8\" style=\"margin-top: 20px; padding-left: 12px;\">\n<h3><strong>Learning Objectives for this module:</strong></h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #ba372a; font-size: 14pt;\">+ &nbsp;</span>Research and understand narrative, language, and user experience in communication design.</p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #ba372a; font-size: 14pt;\">+ &nbsp;</span>Evidence pitching skills to effectively present design concepts.</p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #ba372a; font-size: 14pt;\">+ &nbsp;</span>Proficiently communicate a message and meaning.</p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #ba372a; font-size: 14pt;\">+ &nbsp;</span>Apply strategic frameworks to real-world scenarios to develop practical solutions.</p>\n</article>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n<div class=\"grid-row responsive-padding\" style=\"padding-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; margin-bottom: -50px;\">\n<h3 style=\"padding-left: 12px;\"><strong>Module Content:</strong></h3>\n</div>",
